
Sometimes at night, when the desert wind whips through the tent, Capt. Rosa Kelly  gives a good-night kiss to the soldier huddled in the camouflage sleeping bag next to hers. At 42, Kelly mothers all her soldiers, but this one is special: She is the daughter Kelly lost for six years after her divorce &mdash; Da&ntilde;elea Kelly, now 22. "Da&ntilde;elea is my best friend," Rosa said. "You take her away from me, and you're taking my right arm." 

